<% content_for :title, "Educator Toolkit" %>
<% content_for :og_description, "Resources for teachers to share the Stardance STEM Challenge with their classrooms — free posters, logo, FAQ, and a 2-minute classroom video." %>
<% content_for :twitter_card, "summary_large_image" %>

<%= content_for :stylesheets do %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag "landing", "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>
<% end %>

<% poster_request_url = "#" # Airtable form for free classroom posters %>
<% video_watch_url    = "#" # 2-minute Stardance overview video %>
<% patch_request_url  = "#" # Artemis II sewn mission patch request form %>

<div class="educator-toolkit">
  <%= render "landing/sections/header" %>

  <section class="educator-toolkit__hero">
    <h1 class="educator-toolkit__title">
      Educator <span class="educator-toolkit__title--italic">Toolkit</span>
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="educator-toolkit__resources">
    <h2 class="educator-toolkit__section-title educator-toolkit__section-title--center">Resources</h2>

    <div class="educator-toolkit__resource-layout">
      <a class="educator-toolkit__resource educator-toolkit__resource--featured"
         href="<%= video_watch_url %>"
         target="_blank"
         rel="noopener">
        <div class="educator-toolkit__resource-body">
          <h3 class="educator-toolkit__resource-title">Watch the 2&#8209;minute video</h3>
          <p class="educator-toolkit__resource-meta">
            Two minutes, classroom-ready. Show it before students sign up.
          </p>
        </div>
        <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-action">
          Watch video <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </span>
      </a>

      <div class="educator-toolkit__resource-stack">
        <a class="educator-toolkit__resource educator-toolkit__resource--compact"
           href="<%= poster_request_url %>"
           target="_blank"
           rel="noopener">
          <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-body">
            <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-title">Request free posters</span>
            <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-meta">Free classroom posters, mailed to your door.</span>
          </span>
          <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-action">
            Request posters <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </span>
        </a>

        <a class="educator-toolkit__resource educator-toolkit__resource--compact"
           href="<%= patch_request_url %>"
           target="_blank"
           rel="noopener">
          <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-body">
            <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-title">Get an Artemis II mission patch</span>
            <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-meta">Sewn Artemis II mission patch, mailed after you show the video.</span>
          </span>
          <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-action">
            Request patch <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </span>
        </a>

        <a class="educator-toolkit__resource educator-toolkit__resource--compact"
           href="<%= image_path("landing/header/stardance-logo.png") %>"
           download="stardance-logo.png">
          <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-body">
            <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-title">Download the printable branding kit</span>
            <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-meta">Lorem Ipsum.</span>
          </span>
          <span class="educator-toolkit__resource-action">
            Download Assets <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="educator-toolkit__faq">
    <h2 class="educator-toolkit__faq-title">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="educator-toolkit__faq-list">
      <div class="educator-toolkit__faq-item">
        <h3 class="educator-toolkit__faq-question">What is Stardance?</h3>
        <p class="educator-toolkit__faq-answer">
          Stardance is a free summer STEM challenge for teens ages 13–18, run by
          <a href="https://hackclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hack Club</a>
          in partnership with NASA. Students pick any technical project they want to build
          over the summer (coding, hardware, or otherwise) and get free prizes for showing
          off what they&rsquo;ve made!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="educator-toolkit__faq-item">
        <h3 class="educator-toolkit__faq-question">Who is Hack Club?</h3>
        <p class="educator-toolkit__faq-answer">
          Founded in 2014, Hack Club is a 501(c)(3) non-profit that empowers students to
          create technical projects. Currently with over 100,000 teenage members, our goal
          is to help every student to be able to make incredible things all on their own.
          We get funding from various companies such as AMD and GitHub, as well as private
          donors to be able to offer prizes to any teen who makes awesome projects!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="educator-toolkit__faq-item">
        <h3 class="educator-toolkit__faq-question">How does it actually work?</h3>
        <p class="educator-toolkit__faq-answer">
          Once we launch, students will be able to log into the platform to log their
          projects. They&rsquo;ll do this by installing our Hackatime extension that keeps
          track of their time spent coding (or &lsquo;hacking&rsquo;). Along the way,
          they&rsquo;ll post dev logs to Stardance showing off their project. Once
          they&rsquo;re ready, they&rsquo;ll &ldquo;ship&rdquo; their project by publishing
          it so anyone can see it. From this, they&rsquo;ll get tokens they can use to spend
          in the shop for free prizes like 3d printers, electronics, plushies, and more!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="educator-toolkit__faq-item">
        <h3 class="educator-toolkit__faq-question">Is it open to beginners?</h3>
        <p class="educator-toolkit__faq-answer">
          Yup! We welcome both beginners and experts &mdash; there&rsquo;s no bar for entry
          or competition to get the prizes. Plus, we have tutorials and guided projects so
          anyone can get started making awesome websites, games, hardware, and more!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="educator-toolkit__faq-item">
        <h3 class="educator-toolkit__faq-question">What do I need to do?</h3>
        <p class="educator-toolkit__faq-answer">
          The best part about Stardance is that you don&rsquo;t have to do anything! All we
          need your help with is to spread the word &mdash; otherwise, it&rsquo;s all
          student driven, and we&rsquo;ll be here to support them every step of the way.
          For now, though, putting up posters, sharing the video with your class, and
          letting other teachers know will help us to give this opportunity to as many
          teenagers as possible!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%= render "landing/sections/footer" %>
</div>
